Looking for a quick and tasty midweek dinner option? Try cooking up our Sweet and Sour Pork and Rice in just 20 minutes for a delicious and speedy meal.

== Rice ==

Boil a full #kettle{}.

When boiling, pour the water into a large #saucepan{} with @salt{1/4%tsp} on high heat. Add the @jasmine rice{150%g} and cook for ~{12-13%minutes}.

Drain in a #sieve{} and pop back in the pan. Cover with a #lid{} and leave to the side until ready to serve.

== Mince ==

While the rice cooks, halve, peel and chop the @echalion shallot{1} into small pieces.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{1%drizzle} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

When the oil is hot, add the @British pork mince{240%g} and shallot. Cook until browned, ~{4-5%minutes}. Use a #spoon{} to break up the mince as it cooks, then drain and discard any excess fat.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

Season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}.

== Vegetables ==

Meanwhile, halve the @green pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Chop into 2cm chunks.

Remove the @pineapple rings{1} from the tin, keeping all the juice for later. Cut into small chunks.

Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Roughly chop the @salted peanuts{25%g}.

== Sauce ==

Pour the pineapple juice into a small #bowl{}.

Add the @rice vinegar{30%ml}, @soy sauce{15%ml}, @tomato ketchup{4%tbsp} and @sugar{1/2%tsp}.

Stir to combine, then set aside.

== Cooking ==

Add the pepper and garlic to the mince pan. Cook until softened slightly, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Stir in the sauce and chopped pineapple, then bring to the boil. Cook until slightly thickened, stirring frequently, ~{3-5%minutes}.

Remove from the heat.

> IMPORTANT: The mince is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Taste and season with salt and pepper if needed.

== Serving ==

Fluff up the rice with a fork, then share between your #bowls{}.

Top with the sweet and sour pork, spooning over all the sauce from the pan.

Finish with a sprinkling of peanuts.

Enjoy!